        "Title": "Quesnelia ambrosi",
        "Location": "LOCATION_ROCKY_DUGONG",
        "PublicId": "134532797289",
        "ScenePath": "assembly:/_pro/scenes/missions/Rocky/scene_dugong.entity",
        "TileImage": "$($repository d5a8e140-b14f-4892-8b9b-5b67baf182c9).Image",
        "Description": "Quesnelia ambrosi is a species of bromeliad in the genus Quesnelia.\rThis species is native to the Ambrose Island ecoregion of the Andaman Islands.\rIt has a well-formed rosette of about 25 green leaves. The leaves have lightly serrated edges and are tipped by a sharp spine. The bloom reaches about a foot high. The inflorescence bears dark purple bracts and violet petals. When distilled, the flower can produce a potent, scentless toxin. If ingested, the poison will cause immediate asphyxiation.",
